# Adventure Engine — Changelog since v1.0

## World-Build Wizard & Staging Pipeline
- **Generate → stage → review/edit → commit** workflow for every wizard batch
  (species, factions, locations, characters, bestiary, items). Nothing writes
  to your world until you commit a draft; batch generators are pure and can
  be safely re-run.
- **Context preview** — see the exact, verbatim context a generator will use
  before spending a generation on it.
- **Per-draft regenerate** — reroll a single staged draft in place without
  discarding the rest of the batch.
- **Chat reprompt** — reroll the wizard's last reply without losing the
  conversation.
- **Context budget & distillation** — linked chats are distilled to settled
  facts (not raw deliberation) and the whole context is trimmed to your
  account's actual token ceiling, so smaller-context (Scroll-tier) accounts
  get a working pipeline instead of a silent overflow.
- **Reliability hardening** — a watchdog now recovers from NAI generations
  that occasionally wedge and never return, which used to freeze *all* story
  generation, not just the wizard. A related fix stopped wizard calls from
  stranding for a full 90-second timeout and coming back empty.
- **Character staging** — characters are staged as name + concept; full
  sheet fields are derived at commit time.
- Workspace Help popups were filled out across every workspace (previously
  several fell through to "no help yet").

## Locations & World Graph
- Location generation was consolidated onto one shared entity-creation path
  used by both the wizard batch generator and the in-play "+ New Location"
  flow, so a location is always assembled the same way regardless of how
  it's created.
- Native HUD entry points for spawning sibling/child locations directly from
  the map.

## Factions & Resources
- Faction resources became a proper shared schema (pool / track / discrete)
  editable per-faction, instead of ad hoc fields.
- The Holding Document (party/camp/home/company sheet) and Faction Resources
  moved into their own **Factions Manager** workspace.
- Faction-resource values moved to persistent, story-scoped storage.
- A recursive rule-list editor (`apply_to_pool`) lets an effect's own
  arguments contain another full rule list.

## Holding Document & Player Journal
- The Holding Document gained a bridge-facing projection so the HUD can
  render it without engine round-trips, an ordered section list, and
  stampable notes (mirroring the Journal).
- Player + author identity edits to the Holding (rename, etc.) from both
  surfaces.

## Bestiary & Items
- Reusable NPC and Item template libraries ("Bestiary") feeding the HUD's
  quick "Add NPC" / "Add Item" popups, with brainstorming in the Wizard and
  mechanical fields filled in on the template itself.

## Import / Export & World Sharing
- Smart JSON import now **merges by ID** (upserts) instead of overwriting —
  re-importing a file updates matching records and adds new ones without
  clobbering everything else in your story.

## Actions & Resolution
- Non-dice **player choice** resolution: present an explicit list of
  labeled options instead of always rolling.

## Interface & Navigation
- The old four-tab bar was replaced by a landing-page launcher into
  full-screen workspaces (Roster, Drama, Locations & Entities, Factions
  Manager, Action Studio), each with its own Navigate header and Help button.

## Bridge / HUD
- New **Sakura (Cherry Blossom)** theme, joining Witch's
  Hollow, Runestone, Cyberpunk, and Unicorn Barf, each with theme-specific icon and
  effect layers (e.g. Sakura's glass/rain/koi-pond treatments).
- A built-in **Icon Browser** for previewing the full icon set.
- Sizing and usability fixes to the wizard's in-HUD editing surfaces.
